{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":13767,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-25T15:19:39.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi, i wanted to know is it possible to render ui to texture and pass input events to it? I‚Äôm aiming for something similar to how the in-game computers/panels etc looked in doom 3. Image for reference :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://www.roguevector.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/doom3_console.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"662\" height=\"361\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI couldn‚Äôt find anything after looking at the docs so i‚Äôm assuming  the UI currently only renders to the default backbuffer. If i wanted to modify urho‚Äôs source and add this in how complicated would it be and which parts of the source code should i look into? I‚Äôm new to urho and so far i‚Äôve only had a cursory glance at the source so any help would be really appreciated.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.136Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":415,"reads":66,"readers_count":65,"score":2088.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13769,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T07:34:40.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou can render the UI to texture via a renderpath command, however there isn‚Äôt mapping of input from arbitrary 3D coordinates, or a possibility to have multiple UI hierarchies.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.284Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":64,"readers_count":63,"score":17.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13770,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T07:54:17.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAh okay. So are there any plans to add more features to the default UI in a future release or are users expected to provide their own solution by plugging in another library?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.352Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":63,"readers_count":62,"score":27.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13771,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T08:00:47.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIn-world UI‚Äôs would certainly make sense, and there shouldn‚Äôt be anything impossible with it, it‚Äôs just effort. Urho project operates with limited developers and development time, so the best option always is that if you want something to be implemented, go ahead and do it, and make a pull request when it‚Äôs done. Quite a number of features have been implemented that way.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.421Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":63,"readers_count":62,"score":17.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13772,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T08:10:41.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI understand. I‚Äôll go look into the source and see how it works underneath. Who knows, maybe I‚Äôll be able to add something to it \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/stuck_out_tongue.png?v=5\" title=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":stuck_out_tongue:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThanks for the help!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.483Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":59,"readers_count":58,"score":21.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13773,"name":"Justin Miller","username":"jmiller","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jmiller/{size}/2367_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T12:14:49.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eRelated\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/how-to-best-generate-an-in-game-hud/1684/1\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003eHow to best generate an in-game HUD\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.547Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":58,"readers_count":57,"score":36.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"Justin Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/how-to-best-generate-an-in-game-hud/1684","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"How to best generate an in-game HUD","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":21,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13774,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T12:54:04.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI looked at that thread before asking but thanks for posting. It seems rendering the UI to texture won‚Äôt be that complicated(after i figure out how renderpaths, viewports, views, cameras and rendering tie together  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/stuck_out_tongue.png?v=5\" title=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":stuck_out_tongue:\"\u003e ). I‚Äôm still wondering about how i‚Äôd handle propagating input though!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.618Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":11.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13779,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T19:42:08.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eProgress!!  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smiley.png?v=9\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"http://i.imgur.com/tnTN0PP.png\" title=\"\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/tnTN0PP.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"690\" height=\"387\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1366√ó768\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:24.978Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":16.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://i.imgur.com/tnTN0PP.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"tnTN0PP.png","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13781,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-26T22:50:11.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eLooks good! Nice one.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat was your approach? This is sort of ui is something I have to tackle at some point as well, so I‚Äôd be happy to help out with the effort.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.101Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":57,"readers_count":56,"score":11.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13783,"name":"","username":"Lumak","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/8491ac/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T04:59:50.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOh wow, emacs for windows? That‚Äôs pretty neat and looks great.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.281Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":57,"readers_count":56,"score":16.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":256,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13784,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T05:55:56.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=‚Äúgodan‚Äù]Looks good! Nice one.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat was your approach? This is sort of ui is something I have to tackle at some point as well, so I‚Äôd be happy to help out with the effort.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI used a simple renderpath on a viewport without a camera or scene. Here‚Äôs the renderpath:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;renderpath\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"0 0 0 1\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;command type=\"renderui\" output=\"ui_texture\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/renderpath\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe code is pretty simple as well, this is on a logic component with a plane attached to it\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003evoid Screen_Component::Start()\n{\n\tResourceCache* cache = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;ResourceCache\u0026gt;();\n\tContext* context = GetContext();\n\t\n\tSharedPtr\u0026lt;Texture2D\u0026gt; render_texture(new Texture2D(context));\n\trender_texture-\u0026gt;SetSize(800, 600, Graphics::GetRGBAFormat(), TEXTURE_RENDERTARGET);\n\trender_texture-\u0026gt;SetFilterMode(FILTER_BILINEAR);\n\trender_texture-\u0026gt;SetName(\"ui_texture\");\n\tcache-\u0026gt;AddManualResource(render_texture);\n\n\tSharedPtr\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt; material(new Material(context));\n\tmaterial-\u0026gt;SetTechnique(0, cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Technique\u0026gt;(\"Techniques/DiffSpec.xml\"));\n\tmaterial-\u0026gt;SetTexture(TU_DIFFUSE, render_texture);\n\t\n\tStaticModel* model = GetComponent\u0026lt;StaticModel\u0026gt;();\n\tmodel-\u0026gt;SetMaterial(material);\n\n\tRenderSurface* surface = render_texture-\u0026gt;GetRenderSurface();\n\tSharedPtr\u0026lt;Viewport\u0026gt; ui_viewport(new Viewport(context));\n\tXMLFile* ui_renderpath = cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;XMLFile\u0026gt;(\"RenderPaths/UI_Render.xml\");\n\tui_viewport-\u0026gt;SetRenderPath(ui_renderpath);\n\tui_viewport-\u0026gt;SetRect(IntRect(0, 0, 0, 0));\n\tsurface-\u0026gt;SetViewport(0, ui_viewport);\n\n\tUI* ui = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;UI\u0026gt;();\n\tCursor* cursor = new Cursor(context);\n\tImage* image = cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Image\u0026gt;(\"Textures/UI.png\");\n\tif (image)\n\t{\n\t\tcursor-\u0026gt;DefineShape(CS_NORMAL, image, IntRect(0, 0, 12, 24), IntVector2(0, 0));\n\t\tcursor-\u0026gt;DefineShape(\"Custom\", image, IntRect(12, 0, 12, 36), IntVector2(0, 0));\n\t}\n\tcursor-\u0026gt;SetVisible(false);\n\tui-\u0026gt;SetCursor(cursor);\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere‚Äôs still a lot left to do however. If the plane goes out of the view the UI is drawn to the screen like normal. I have to come up with some way to disable the UI when the player is not looking. Since i plan on having most, if not all UI in world space, this won‚Äôt be too complicated. There are probably other issues to resolve as well which i haven‚Äôt encountered yet but this seems like a good enough start. It would‚Äôve been really nice if there could‚Äôve been multiple UI hierarchies though, it seems i‚Äôll either have to modify urho‚Äôs source or i‚Äôll have to figure out some other hack and simulate it by having other empty UI nodes attached to the root node and turn them on and off when i need.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Lumak\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/8491ac/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Lumak:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOh wow, emacs for windows? That‚Äôs pretty neat and looks great.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYeah, i have to basically use emacs everywhere after getting ‚Äúemacs fingers‚Äù, no other text editor feels right, and i‚Äôm not even that good with emacs! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/laughing.png?v=10\" title=\":laughing:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":laughing:\"\u003e That being said, the consolas font looks even better in emacs for some reason. Windows is no fun at all but i have to use it because performance on linux is not that great on my craptop(Intel HD 4000)  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/stuck_out_tongue.png?v=10\" title=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":stuck_out_tongue:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.365Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":57,"readers_count":56,"score":16.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13785,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T08:12:26.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf you want to implement this properly I believe you have to tackle the multiple UI hierarchies issue, for example allow a scene component to store a UI root element, and have it separate from the existing UI root that would be rendered to the backbuffer. This probably includes more substantial code changes. For the existing UI there‚Äôs a simple logic that if it‚Äôs not rendered anywhere else by a renderpath command, then it will be rendered to the backbuffer, which you‚Äôre seeing here.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.444Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":15.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13786,"name":"","username":"bluerriq","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/fbc32d/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T08:44:05.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm still researching whether or not to go with world-space UI‚Äôs everywhere though and so far i haven‚Äôt seen a lot of games going with this approach and for good reason. For simple UI elements like large buttons etc this approach would be better but for more complicated UIs this approach could get annoying. I suppose i‚Äôll have to strike a balance between 3d and 2d UIs by using text3d/textures for worldspace elements and 2d UI for the rest to not affect the immersion and go for the same look as fallout‚Äôs pipboy :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"http://vignette3.wikia.nocookie.net/fallout/images/7/76/Pip-Boy_3000.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110712154420\" title=\"\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://vignette3.wikia.nocookie.net/fallout/images/7/76/Pip-Boy_3000.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110712154420\" alt=\"\" width=\"690\" height=\"388\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1024√ó576\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFood for thought!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEither way, personal musing on UIs aside, you‚Äôre correct, there‚Äôs no going around multiple hierarchies if this way of handling UIs is required.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.505Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":48,"readers_count":47,"score":19.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://vignette3.wikia.nocookie.net/fallout/images/7/76/Pip-Boy_3000.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110712154420","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":558,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13788,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T12:32:07.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWould having more control over the transform that‚Äôs passed to the Batch class do anything? E.g.:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003evoid UIBatch::AddQuad(const Matrix3x4\u0026amp; transform, int x, int y, int width, int height, int texOffsetX, int texOffsetY,\n    int texWidth, int texHeight)\n{\n    unsigned topLeftColor, topRightColor, bottomLeftColor, bottomRightColor;\n\n    if (!useGradient_)\n    {\n        // If alpha is 0, nothing will be rendered, so do not add the quad\n        if (!(color_ \u0026amp; 0xff000000))\n            return;\n\n        topLeftColor = color_;\n        topRightColor = color_;\n        bottomLeftColor = color_;\n        bottomRightColor = color_;\n    }\n    else\n    {\n        topLeftColor = GetInterpolatedColor(x, y);\n        topRightColor = GetInterpolatedColor(x + width, y);\n        bottomLeftColor = GetInterpolatedColor(x, y + height);\n        bottomRightColor = GetInterpolatedColor(x + width, y + height);\n    }\n\n    Vector3 v1 = (transform * Vector3((float)x, (float)y, 0.0f)) - posAdjust;\n    Vector3 v2 = (transform * Vector3((float)x + (float)width, (float)y, 0.0f)) - posAdjust;\n    Vector3 v3 = (transform * Vector3((float)x, (float)y + (float)height, 0.0f)) - posAdjust;\n    Vector3 v4 = (transform * Vector3((float)x + (float)width, (float)y + (float)height, 0.0f)) - posAdjust;\n\n...\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf this could provide full 3d positioning of the quad, it seems like this would go a long way towards 3d camera space ui. Doesn‚Äôt handle occluding geometry, though‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.637Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":14.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13789,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T12:48:01.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe problem with free form UI transform is that you can no longer use scissor, which means listviews etc. would not be able to mask the scrolling content properly. To keep things working right I‚Äôd rather recommend rendering to a texture first.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNaturally that will cause a video RAM problem if you have for example a building with 100‚Äôs of computer screens and each allocates its own unique texture, so in that case a more advanced allocation system is needed, that throws out the unneeded UI textures.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.701Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":24.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13791,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T13:40:46.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eJust to pursue the UI transform a bit more: What about resizing the Scissor to the projected transform/quad size? Or even, just use whatever Scissor was calculated before transforming the quad. For sure, in the worst case, the quad while be positioned such that the scissor is not too effective. But on the other hand, the Scissor test should still catch conditions like the UI element being off screen, or lots and lots of text not being inside the UI size, etc‚Ä¶Basically, you just do the scissor test on the inverse of the transform.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":16,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.867Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":8.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13792,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-09-27T13:55:06.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt‚Äôs a fixed hardware feature and only rectangular, so it wouldn‚Äôt work for example with a ListView rotated 45 degrees, and you‚Äôd have items leaking out. I don‚Äôt even care for optimization in that regard, but correctness.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":17,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:25.933Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":45,"readers_count":44,"score":9.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2268,"topic_slug":"render-ui-to-texture","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[13767,13769,13770,13771,13772,13773,13774,13779,13781,13783,13784,13785,13786,13788,13789,13791,13792]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,2250],[2,2249],[10,2248]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7100,"title":"UI Sprites - Wrapping/Repeating Texture","fancy_title":"UI Sprites - Wrapping/Repeating Texture","slug":"ui-sprites-wrapping-repeating-texture","posts_count":3,"reply_count":0,"highest_post_number":3,"image_url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/5/5d95641f056666c79c67a12520276d2d9f4729ae.png","created_at":"2021-12-15T20:32:37.485Z","last_posted_at":"2021-12-16T03:28:29.146Z","bumped":true,"bump